  "title": "Physiotherapist / Occupational Therapist",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Description:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Conduct thorough occupational/physiotherapy assessments during client admissions, periodic care reviews, and at discharge.</li><li>Select and implement tailored outcome measures to gauge therapy progress and effectiveness.</li><li>Collaborate with clients and stakeholders to develop personalized and achievable goals.</li><li>Design evidence-based therapy interventions that prioritize individual client needs and preferences.</li><li>Maintain accurate documentation of assessment results, therapy plans, interventions, and outcomes.</li><li>Effectively communicate assessment findings, intervention plans, and discharge strategies to clients and relevant parties.</li><li>Ensure proper utilization and client training on rehabilitation equipment, including advanced technological aids.</li><li>Provide recommendations for assistive devices and equipment as needed for enhanced mobility and functionality.</li><li>Develop comprehensive discharge and continuity of care plans to support clients post-therapy.</li><li>Foster community integration through strategic partnerships with local organizations and services.</li><li>Contribute actively to case discussions within the care team for holistic client management.</li><li>Offer guidance and support in training Therapy Assistants to uphold quality standards in therapy delivery.</li></ul><p><u><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Degree in Physiotherapy or Occupational Therapy</li><li>Must be registered with Singapore Allied Health Professional Council (AHPC).</li></ul><p>To submit your application, please apply online <a href=\"mailto:apply@rn-care.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>apply@rn-care.com</strong></a><strong> </strong>or call <a href=\"tel:+(65) 6223 0323\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">+(65) 6223 0323</a> for private and confidential discussion.</p><p>Your interest will be treated with the strictest of confidence. We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified or contacted.</p><p><strong>RN Care Pte. Ltd</strong><br /><strong>EA License No: 17C8900</strong></p>",
